    subject_key: 'elephant', subject: 'Elephant', category: 'animal', age_group: '4-6', language: 'english',
    title: 'The Elephant and the Ants',
    body: `A mighty elephant named Bhola loved to stomp through the forest. THUMP! THUMP! One day his big foot nearly flattened a busy anthill. "Please, friend, walk gently — this is our home!" squeaked the tiny ants. Bhola laughed. "You are so small, why should I care?" and stomped away proudly.\n\nA few days later, a thorn jabbed deep into Bhola's foot. He could not reach it, and it hurt terribly. Who came to help? The very ants he had ignored! Together they nibbled and tugged until — pop! — out came the thorn.\n\nBhola was amazed. "I am sorry I called you too small to matter," he said. From then on, big Bhola always walked gently, and the ants were his dearest friends.`,
