    subject_key: 'elephant', subject: 'Elephant', category: 'animal', age_group: '7-9', language: 'english',
    title: 'Ganesha and the Race Around the World',
    body: `Long ago, the gentle elephant-headed Ganesha lived with his brother Kartikeya and their parents, Shiva and Parvati. One day a sage brought a single, special mango — the fruit of wisdom. "It cannot be cut or shared," he said. "It is for whichever of your sons proves the wiser."\n\nShiva and Parvati thought of a contest. "Whoever travels around the whole world three times and returns first shall have the mango." At once, Kartikeya leapt onto his swift peacock and soared into the sky, racing over mountains, oceans, and forests.\n\nGanesha looked at his small mouse and smiled. He could never win such a race that way. So he sat and thought. Then, quietly, Ganesha rose and walked slowly around his mother and father — once, twice, three times — and folded his hands.\n\n"You have not gone anywhere!" said Shiva. "But I have," said Ganesha gently. "My parents are my whole world. To walk around you is to walk around all of creation." Shiva and Parvati's eyes shone with joy.\n\nWhen Kartikeya returned, tired and dusty, he found Ganesha already holding the mango — not because he was faster, but because he was wise and loving. And everyone agreed: true wisdom sees what matters most.`,
