    subject_key: 'fox', subject: 'Fox', category: 'animal', age_group: '4-6', language: 'english',
    title: 'The Jackal and the Drum',
    body: `A hungry jackal wandered into an empty field, looking for something to eat. Suddenly he heard a frightening sound — DHOOM! DHOOM! DHOOM! It boomed louder than any animal he had ever heard. His legs shook. "That must be a huge, fierce beast! It will surely gobble me up!"\n\nHe almost ran away. But his tummy was so empty, and he was curious too. "Before I run," he thought, "let me at least peek at this giant creature." Carefully, quietly, he crept toward the sound, his heart going pit-a-pat.\n\nHe pushed through the tall grass — and what did he find? Only an old drum, lying beside a tree! When the wind blew, a branch tapped it: DHOOM! "Ha!" laughed the jackal, weak with relief. "Such a big, scary noise, and nothing inside but air!"\n\nAnd nearby, he found a sack of food the drummers had left behind. Because he was brave enough to look instead of just run, the jackal ate a happy meal that day.`,
