    body: `Two friends were walking through a forest, promising to always help each other. Suddenly, a big bear came lumbering along the path! One friend quickly scrambled up a tall tree, forgetting all about the other.\n\nThe second friend could not climb, and the bear was very near. Then he remembered something his grandmother had told him: bears do not bother those who lie still. So he dropped to the ground and lay as still as a stone, holding his breath.\n\nThe big bear ambled over and sniffed his ear, his hair, his face... but the friend did not move a muscle. Thinking him asleep and no fun at all, the bear shrugged and wandered away into the trees.\n\nWhen it was safe, the friend in the tree climbed down. "What did the bear whisper in your ear?" he asked. The other friend smiled. "The bear gave me good advice. He said never to travel with a friend who runs away and leaves you behind." The first friend looked down, ashamed — and promised that he would never abandon a friend in trouble again.`,
