    title: 'The Proud Horse and the Donkey',
    body: `A fine, glossy horse lived on a farm beside a humble donkey. All day the donkey carried heavy sacks of grain, while the horse pranced about, proud of his shiny coat. "Why bother working so hard?" the horse scoffed. "Look how grand and free I am!" The donkey only smiled and kept plodding along.\n\nOne hot afternoon, the farmer needed many sacks taken to the market, and the donkey was already tired. "Today," said the farmer, "the horse will help carry the load." The horse's eyes went wide. The sacks were so heavy! His back ached, his legs trembled, and the road felt endless.\n\nThe donkey walked quietly beside him, sharing the load and the path. By the time they reached the market, the proud horse was puffing and dusty. "I'm sorry I laughed at you," he said at last. "Your work is far harder than it looks." From that day, the horse helped with the heavy sacks too — and learned that there is real strength, and real dignity, in honest hard work.`,
