    title: "Gauri's Cool Shade",
    body: `In a sunny village field stood a kind cow named Gauri, beneath a single shady tree. One blazing summer, the field grew hot and dry. A little sparrow panted in the heat. "Come, rest in my shade," said Gauri, swishing her tail to make a cool breeze.\n\nSoon a tired squirrel came, then a thirsty grasshopper, then a wandering goat — and Gauri welcomed them all into the cool shade beside her. She never said, "There isn't room," or "Find your own tree." She simply made space for one more, and one more.\n\nIn return, the sparrow sang sweet songs, the squirrel shared nuts, and the goat shooed away the buzzing flies. The hot days passed pleasantly for everyone, because Gauri shared her shade freely. "When you give with an open heart," she said, smiling, "you are never left alone." And indeed, the generous cow was surrounded by friends all summer long.`,
